+# API rate limiting
+
+Every authenticated API client is subject to a per-minute request ceiling
+enforced by the `RateLimiter` Rack middleware. Counters live in Redis and reset
+on a fixed 60-second window, so a client gets a fresh budget each minute.
+
+## Tiers
+
+| Tier         | Requests / minute |
+|--------------|-------------------|
+| `standard`   | 60                |
+| `pro`        | 600               |
+| `enterprise` | 6,000             |
+
+A client's effective limit is the higher of its tier default and the
+`requests_per_minute` override column, so a single noisy integration can be
+lifted without promoting it to a whole new tier.
+
+## Response headers
+
+Every API response carries the client's current budget:
+
+- `X-RateLimit-Limit` — the ceiling for the current window.
+- `X-RateLimit-Remaining` — requests left before a `429` is returned.
+
+When the ceiling is exceeded the middleware responds with `429 Too Many
+Requests`, a `Retry-After: 60` header, and a JSON body of
+`{ "error": "rate_limit_exceeded" }`.
